In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki discussed a range of topics. She mentioned that the White House Task Force on Worker Organizing and Empowerment, led by Vice President Kamala Harris and Labor Secretary Marty Walsh, released a report with recommendations to promote worker organizing and collective bargaining. Psaki also noted that the Department of Agriculture will invest $1 billion in partnerships to support climate-smart farmers, ranchers, and forest landowners. In addition, she mentioned that the United States will not be sending a diplomatic or official delegation to the Beijing Olympics due to concerns about human rights abuses in China, but still supports Team USA athletes. Psaki also addressed questions about the reprimand of Dr. Eric Lander, the nominee for the Director of the Office of Science and Technology Policy, for inappropriate behavior and reiterated the President's commitment to a respectful work environment. She discussed the ongoing tensions with Russia and Ukraine, stating that the US is pursuing a two-track approach of deterrence and diplomacy. Psaki also addressed questions about mask mandates in schools, potential sanctions on Russia, and the Supreme Court nomination process.